cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.IT

This paper presents a new protocol for WiFi that uses deep learning to mitigate interference and improve throughput. As such, it is likely to fall under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper heavily relies on machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also be classified under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also discusses security and authentication, which could place it under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. The use of deep learning for signal classification and channel selection also suggests that it could be classified under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper discusses modulation and coding schemes, which could place it under the Information Theory (cs.IT) category.
